The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, March 20, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, March 19: Sleuths swooped down today on the hideout of Pradeep Jain at Gariahat in south Calcutta and arrested him for running a cricket betting racket. Jain, 40, has been remanded in police custody till March 28. Three mobile phones and two sim cards were recovered from him.

 ?Jain was involved in betting even during the ongoing Indo-Pak match at Eden Gardens,? said Gyanwant Singh, the chief of the city police?s detective department.

 Calcutta: Two groups of doctors of the Indian Medical Association clashed on Saturday afternoon during the election of office bearers for the Calcutta branch. Police said Dr Kishan Pradhan, contesting the post of secretary and Dr Subhas Dasgupta, contesting the assistant secretary?s post, were roughed up by doctors supporting the Trinamul Congress.

 Calcutta: Farukh Hossein, an MA student, was arrested by police for kidnapping 16-year-old Sushmita Chatterjee. Police nabbed Hossein at Chatna in the Rajarhat police station area and rescued the girl.

 Calcutta: Ballygunje police on Saturday arrested Kaushik Nath from Manoharpukur Road on charges of cheating customers of Rs 2 crore. Police officials claimed Nath had been working as an agent for two banks, including a private one, for a few years and would walk away with money meant for housing loans. The police are probing if bank officials are also involved.




